p.seg:
The fortress is relatively small. The name “Florentin” originates from the late antique term “Florenitiana,” which was referenced by Procopius in the 6th century. Researchers believe the fortress was abandoned following the settlement of the Slavs. Unfortunately, no traces of the ancient and medieval structures remain. The existing remnants date from the post-15th to 16th centuries and are thought to have been constructed no earlier than the 12th to 13th centuries.
See: Гюзелев, В. Български средновековни градове и крепости, т.I. Варна, 1981 г., с. 94-97;
https://www.bulgariancastles.com/s-florentin-krepost-florentiana/
